### Ok so the huge mess is here
# We can't easily change religious opinion, especially if we want it to be as gradual as a 0-100% scale
# So we need 100 doctrines to properly represent your view on a faith...
# ... But we don't just care about your faith, every faith in the game needs its own view on every other faith...
# ... So each faith needs 100 doctrines to represent other faiths opinion of them

# So, how it works:
# Your faith receives a unique doctrine, hostility_doctrine_id_X
# Other faiths get a doctrine representing their opinion of you, hostility_doctrine_id_X_hostility_Y
# X can go as high as the total number of faiths, and Y has a range of 1-100
# So we need X * 100 doctrines
# Fun!

hostility_doctrine_id = {
	group = "hostility"
	is_available_on_create = { always = no } # Given via event
	
	## Let's say we can handle 200 faiths
	# That's a very high estimate, but that way we have a lot of room
